I learned early on in my career that a true DJ needs to be able to build and draw people into their room if it’s a multi-room party. There were honestly around 20 people in my room before I started playing as Skream b2b @interplanetary_criminal93 were playing in the other room at the same time…but this is what it became within 30 minutes. Glad to see I still have my basic skills as a “puller” intact. 😉
Such a humbling, exciting and spiritual vibe this one! Thanks again @skreamizm @thebeamslondon and the dancers/vibers. 
So many of my friends/Fam in attendance as well @mmmvita @remtingsz which always makes it extra special. Added bonus was meeting @djnookie who came through on recommendation by the man, my brother @mrgoldie -Big Ups

The best Christmas in 2019. We hosted some of our Homeless Homies to a two night hotel stay at the Bilderberg Hotel. Joined by our rave family, we had Christmas Eve dinner at Wagamama Euweplein, then we checked in at the hotel where we occupied a whole wing at the hotel. Everyone had a nice bath, a good sleep, then we met up for Christmas breakfast where we shared stories. Everyone left to go to their Christmas parties and when they returned, we had Christmas Dinner. The Homies gave me flowers and shared their presents with us. It was the most memorable, most special holidays we ever experienced. Truly, the holidays is about being of service to those less fortunate.

Give love.

We closed out this year with such a vibe on NYE!! 2022 brought me many things that I’m extremely grateful for. One is seeing Further evolve from a sit down, socially distanced escape from lockdown to a full blown club event. I say event because Further is more than just a night, it’s a journey, a vibe, a gathering of alike souls seeking to create a moment in time. I am very proud of what we’ve accomplished so far. With the help of my other/better half Ahnne (who works tirelessly to make things happen), Radion and our team I am able to bring long awaited concepts and ideas to fruition. 🙏🏾❤️

And here are some other blessings 2022 brought:
Being able to help raise over €30,000 for Ukrainian aide. 

@myhomelesshomies fundraiser (during ADE) to benefit @regenboog020 . 

Time with the Mrs. @i.am.ahnne and our amazing extended family. 

Being asked to do a @palaceskateboards x @applemusic spatial audio mix. 

Being named 1 of 100 of the world’s best DJs by @djmagofficial . 

Our @djbonegoesfurther events at @radionamsterdam . 🙌🏾

DJ Bone b2b @mrgoldie tour. 

Being part of the DJ Bone x Palace x Detroit Tigers campaign. 
 
Official launch of @docciroc . 

My Black Market EP release on @fabric_records . 

I want to thank all of you who support me for making this a great year! I’m humbled by the power of what can happen when people come together as one through music. I wish everyone safety, success and fulfillment this year. And if you need to feel that vibe you know where to come. 

Stay up and KeepDeep,
🦴

FURTHER presents: Kings of Kingsnight
 
Our way of honouring the KINGS of techno, house, electro, ghetto-tech and booty. 

As we prepare for another Kings Day in the Netherlands, DJ Bone and FURTHER have curated a unique night for the true kings of electronic music’s most thrilling & influential dancefloor genres, with an all-Detroit line-up never seen before in Amsterdam.

👑🔥🖤

@detroit_in_effect is true Electro royalty: one of the foundational artists in creating that ghetto groove that shakes asses and shapes minds, standing as an essential figure in the Motor City.

Underground techno champion @djbone313’s impeccable mastery of the decks is timeless, with innovative fader chops and hypnotic selections that never let you stop moving.

Futuristic electro master @dj_stingray_313 has been expertly mixing electro and techno to rapturous audiences for decades, criss-crossing European and American styles in a way only a true maestro could.

Groovy house selector @docciroc, the alter ego of DJ Bone, will be giving us that funky, deep soul we all need.

Soulful techno and house connoisseur @moodymann313’s remarkable selections bring you into the world of Detroit funk with a captivating scope of sounds.

Also in attendance we have our incredible resident kings & queens bringing that quality FURTHER flavour: @azucy_ and @jantjevandebuurt, @mrandygram & Veroon (@freddie_van_waning), @talordj, @tonio.flaco and our new welcome additions, @thisistanua and @_yetimindtricks.

FURTHER is a journey.
FURTHER is an experience.
FURTHER is a vibe.

This is not one you will want to miss as you prepare your Kings Day celebrations.

Thank you @djmagofficial 

This is exciting and especially humbling. 

When my Manager told me that they wanted to put me on a cover I asked if she was serious. Not that I didn’t think I’ve earned it, it’s just that seeing an underground artist on the cover is a very rare sight. 

My 35 year career is older than the majority of the mag’s readers yet the vibes we create together make me feel younger every time I play. 

I enjoy being true to the roots while still experimenting and pushing past what is currently accepted as DJing. 

For me it’s always been about the music and the art of DJing. Never sought fame, never followed trends, just wanted to be able to make a meaningful career out of doing what I love. 

Thanks again DJ Mag for shining a very bright light on this underground artist. I very much appreciate this. 

Endless love and respect to my wife Ahnne, my FURTHER Family and everyone who enjoys, dances to and supports what I do, who I am or what I’m about. 

And remember it’s always ok to be your authentic self because…

The music > antics. 
Talent > hype. 
Longevity > being hot right now. 

Plot your own unique course and be greater than anyone else thinks you should be. 
Go FURTHER. 

DJ Bone 
Going Further
DJ Mag April 2023

Get your copy via djmagshop.com

📸 @timbuiting

#djbonegoesfurther

“Further started from his desire to get back ‘to listening to loud music’, bringing nightlife into the daytime via physically distanced sit down events. 

“You’ve got 75 people sat on couches and beanbags,” he says, setting the scene.

“He felt like ‘a professor’… It’s a reminder of how timeless Detroit’s early output is, Bone peppering in stories of its creators as he plays.

“I’m never in doubt of myself, my skills, my abilities,” he says of his DJing and production. Yet he still has “a lot of Detroit in me that’s just set in my ways, especially when it comes to my belief system”.

Read the whole interview with DJ Mag by going to djmagshop.com, and ordering your magazine copy.

Gratitude not attitude:

I am so thankful for all of the wonderful people in my life, for this journey and where it’s taken/taking me! 
I am Me, simple as that. I wake up and do what I do every day…be myself. Don’t let anything or anyone sidetrack you from being You.

This week’s guest on the Not A Diving Podcast is DJ Bone

The majority of DJs spent the pandemic mostly of stood in front of a camera, attempting to perform the impossible task of transplanting a rave into the bedrooms of the few people lucky enough to be watching at the other end of a fibre optic cable.

We are only beginning to come to terms with the implications of what the failure of that approach have had for our culture, but @djbone313 did something completely different. 

'Further' was a hugely successful series of events which combined music, talking, and a bit of socially-distanced vibing out. At Radion in Amsterdam, there was a real effort made to add something extra within the constraints of some of the most draconian lockdown measures anywhere in the world. 

He also just released an album of the same name as those events, which he sees as jumping off point to his career even at this relatively advanced stage. 

We discuss that in detail, as well as those events, and what they mean in the context of what he's done in music since the 90s. 

We also discuss his roots as a party-goer in Detroit, the wider state of Techno and dance music generally today, and what needs to change to get back on track after a few years of real turmoil. 

This was a great conversation in which we dig into some really meaty areas, and get some incredible detail on the birthplace of Techno. 

Get it wherever you get your podcasts!
Happy Pops Day, @djbone313!!!

My wife and friends are the best!!
On Friday Ric and @veggiebecky313 flew to DC to see/hear me at @flashclubdc and my dear friends Laura and Kyle pulled up too! Played for an amazing crowd at packed Flash, then flew to Miami on no sleep 😳. Had a couple hours disco-nap then had to wake up for dinner. I was super tired heading to dinner, had no idea that my wife @i.am.ahnne and my early DJ mentor @dj_sneakypete had planned a surprise for me. 
Walked into the restaurant only to see that Pete had organized for five of our homies from the Music Institute days in Detroit to fly in for the gig. 🥲
This means so much to me, to have this level of love and support from true friends that I consider family. 
Last night was such a great journey. @staminafl are the template for what underground parties in Miami should be. I love their crowd of beautiful, music loving, dancing, free and open peeps!!
Shoutout to Pete, Jon, Randall, Sam, Squirt, Lamar, Bruce, Ric, Becky, (of course) Ahnne, Quinto restaurant,  @eastmia FlashDC and StaminaFL 🙏🏾

Detroit, you welcomed me back with so much love, thank you! Feels like our true Detroit vibe has been reignited!!

My Replicant Self
DJ Bone
The Portal EP
FR-002 DJ Bone Presents FURTHER

Link to Stream in Bio

https://orcd.co/fr-02djbone

~~~~~~~~~~~~

FURTHER’s first official release is both a signature EP from a rising star and a declaration of intent from the label itself: ‘We Ain’t Like Them’ sees Yeti Mind Tricks kickstart the label with three thrilling original cuts which perfectly showcase the producer’s UK-meets-Detroit style, complimented by a relentless remix from Bone himself.  The Glasgow-based producer & curator/resident of the city’s long-running BASSment club night came to Bone’s attention in 2022 following a pair of EPs for DJ 3000’s Motech label. Having connected via Instagram, Yeti sent the demos which became FURTHER’s inaugural release.
 
Dropping on the same day, DJ Bone’s ‘The Portal’ EP’s immediate arrival will provide huge excitement for fans eager to hear his first material of this new era. With a harder edge than what was found on his recent album, the four tracks here see Bone adding new textures and techniques to his sonic arsenal, while being no less able to find transcendent moments in the midst of the intensity.
 
DJ Bone says:
I decided to kick off my new label FURTHER with a release from Yeti Mind Tricks titled ‘We Ain’t Like Them’, due to those words uttered throughout the track. Yeti sent it to me as a demo and after playing it out a few times I knew that this was more than a track: it was a raw and to-the-point description of myself and the entire FURTHER crew.
 
The second release will be from yours truly. The Portal EP steps into new territory for me, and marks the exciting launch of this endeavor of pushing things further than I ever have before.
 
Expect unconventional maneuvers.
Expect the unknown and unheard, cuz We Ain’t Like Them.

I am very proud to announce the launch of my own channel/station/curator page:  𝐃𝐉 𝐁𝐨𝐧𝐞 𝐆𝐨𝐞𝐬 𝐅𝐔𝐑𝐓𝐇𝐄𝐑 on @applemusic!

I knew we needed a place, a channel for the underground to represent…for Detroit techno, real house music, electro and other original and experimental genres to be heard, discovered (if you’re new), appreciated and felt. Apple Music heard the call and came through.
